>         You have mentioned that in your setting  width_inc = 9 .
>         How to set this ? If it set to 9 this porblem will go ?

The only way to modify this width is by choosing a different font.
It is actually the width of a single character in this case.
Changing the font won't help though, unless you can live with
characters that are only one pixel wide ;-)

The only workaround I can think of is limiting the size of the
nedit window with something similar to

  Style nedit MaxWindowSize 99 10000

This limits the width of the nedit window to 99% of the screen
width (plus borders).  The nedit window will still grow, but not
as much as before.

Bye

