Doh.  Boolean values can't be 0 or one.  Nothing of the above
could have worked.  You to use symbolic names like "True" and
"False".  Anyway, I've fixed it.  The argument can now be either
a number (0/1/-1) or a symbol (Match/NoMatch/Error).  The example
works now for me with both commands.

